message.content:
In this scenario, there were initially three killers in the room. One of the killers was killed by someone entering the room. After this event, two killers remain in the room.

To break it down:

1. Initial number of killers: 3
2. Number of killings that took place: 1 (the person who entered killed one of the original killers)
3. Remaining number of killers: 3 - 1 = 2

So, there are two killers left in the room after the incident.
